\title{Clinicaltrials Database}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{description}{"Query ClinicalTrials.gov via API v2. Search trials by condition, drug, location, status, or phase. Retrieve trial details by NCT ID, export data, for clinical research and patient matching."}

\subtree{
\title{ClinicalTrials.gov Database}
\subtree{
\title{Overview}
\p{ClinicalTrials.gov is a comprehensive registry of clinical studies conducted worldwide, maintained by the U.S. National Library of Medicine. Access API v2 to search for trials, retrieve detailed study information, filter by various criteria, and export data for analysis. The API is public (no authentication required) with rate limits of ~50 requests per minute, supporting JSON and CSV formats.}
}

\subtree{
\title{When to Use This Skill}
\p{This skill should be used when working with clinical trial data in scenarios such as:}

\ul{
\li{\strong{Patient matching} - Finding recruiting trials for specific conditions or patient populations}
\li{\strong{Research analysis} - Analyzing clinical trial trends, outcomes, or study designs}
\li{\strong{Drug/intervention research} - Identifying trials testing specific drugs or interventions}
\li{\strong{Geographic searches} - Locating trials in specific locations or regions}
\li{\strong{Sponsor/organization tracking} - Finding trials conducted by specific institutions}
\li{\strong{Data export} - Extracting clinical trial data for further analysis or reporting}
\li{\strong{Trial monitoring} - Tracking status updates or results for specific trials}
\li{\strong{Eligibility screening} - Reviewing inclusion/exclusion criteria for trials}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Quick Start}
\subtree{
\title{Basic Search Query}
\p{Search for clinical trials using the helper script:}

\pre{\startverb
cd scientific-databases/clinicaltrials-database/scripts
python3 query_clinicaltrials.py
\stopverb}

\p{Or use Python directly with the \code{\startverb requests\stopverb} library:}

\pre{\startverb
import requests

url = "https://clinicaltrials.gov/api/v2/studies"
params = {
    "query.cond": "breast cancer",
    "filter.overallStatus": "RECRUITING",
    "pageSize": 10
}

response = requests.get(url, params=params)
data = response.json()

print(f"Found {data['totalCount']} trials")
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Retrieve Specific Trial}
\p{Get detailed information about a trial using its NCT ID:}

\pre{\startverb
import requests

nct_id = "NCT04852770"
url = f"https://clinicaltrials.gov/api/v2/studies/{nct_id}"

response = requests.get(url)
study = response.json()

# Access specific modules
title = study['protocolSection']['identificationModule']['briefTitle']
status = study['protocolSection']['statusModule']['overallStatus']
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Core Capabilities}
\subtree{
\title{1. Search by Condition/Disease}
\p{Find trials studying specific medical conditions or diseases using the \code{\startverb query.cond\stopverb} parameter.}

\p{\strong{Example: Find recruiting diabetes trials}}

\pre{\startverb
from scripts.query_clinicaltrials import search_studies

results = search_studies(
    condition="type 2 diabetes",
    status="RECRUITING",
    page_size=20,
    sort="LastUpdatePostDate:desc"
)

print(f"Found {results['totalCount']} recruiting diabetes trials")
for study in results['studies']:
    protocol = study['protocolSection']
    nct_id = protocol['identificationModule']['nctId']
    title = protocol['identificationModule']['briefTitle']
    print(f"{nct_id}: {title}")
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Common use cases:}}

\ul{
\li{Finding trials for rare diseases}
\li{Identifying trials for comorbid conditions}
\li{Tracking trial availability for specific diagnoses}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{2. Search by Intervention/Drug}
\p{Search for trials testing specific interventions, drugs, devices, or procedures using the \code{\startverb query.intr\stopverb} parameter.}

\p{\strong{Example: Find Phase 3 trials testing Pembrolizumab}}

\pre{\startverb
from scripts.query_clinicaltrials import search_studies

results = search_studies(
    intervention="Pembrolizumab",
    status=["RECRUITING", "ACTIVE_NOT_RECRUITING"],
    page_size=50
)

# Filter by phase in results
phase3_trials = [
    study for study in results['studies']
    if 'PHASE3' in study['protocolSection'].get('designModule', {}).get('phases', [])
]
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Common use cases:}}

\ul{
\li{Drug development tracking}
\li{Competitive intelligence for pharmaceutical companies}
\li{Treatment option research for clinicians}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{3. Geographic Search}
\p{Find trials in specific locations using the \code{\startverb query.locn\stopverb} parameter.}

\p{\strong{Example: Find cancer trials in New York}}

\pre{\startverb
from scripts.query_clinicaltrials import search_studies

results = search_studies(
    condition="cancer",
    location="New York",
    status="RECRUITING",
    page_size=100
)

# Extract location details
for study in results['studies']:
    locations_module = study['protocolSection'].get('contactsLocationsModule', {})
    locations = locations_module.get('locations', [])
    for loc in locations:
        if 'New York' in loc.get('city', ''):
            print(f"{loc['facility']}: {loc['city']}, {loc.get('state', '')}")
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Common use cases:}}

\ul{
\li{Patient referrals to local trials}
\li{Geographic trial distribution analysis}
\li{Site selection for new trials}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{4. Search by Sponsor/Organization}
\p{Find trials conducted by specific organizations using the \code{\startverb query.spons\stopverb} parameter.}

\p{\strong{Example: Find trials sponsored by NCI}}

\pre{\startverb
from scripts.query_clinicaltrials import search_studies

results = search_studies(
    sponsor="National Cancer Institute",
    page_size=100
)

# Extract sponsor information
for study in results['studies']:
    sponsor_module = study['protocolSection']['sponsorCollaboratorsModule']
    lead_sponsor = sponsor_module['leadSponsor']['name']
    collaborators = sponsor_module.get('collaborators', [])
    print(f"Lead: {lead_sponsor}")
    if collaborators:
        print(f"  Collaborators: {', '.join([c['name'] for c in collaborators])}")
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Common use cases:}}

\ul{
\li{Tracking institutional research portfolios}
\li{Analyzing funding organization priorities}
\li{Identifying collaboration opportunities}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{5. Filter by Study Status}
\p{Filter trials by recruitment or completion status using the \code{\startverb filter.overallStatus\stopverb} parameter.}

\p{\strong{Valid status values:}}

\ul{
\li{\code{\startverb RECRUITING\stopverb} - Currently recruiting participants}
\li{\code{\startverb NOT_YET_RECRUITING\stopverb} - Not yet open for recruitment}
\li{\code{\startverb ENROLLING_BY_INVITATION\stopverb} - Only enrolling by invitation}
\li{\code{\startverb ACTIVE_NOT_RECRUITING\stopverb} - Active but no longer recruiting}
\li{\code{\startverb SUSPENDED\stopverb} - Temporarily halted}
\li{\code{\startverb TERMINATED\stopverb} - Stopped prematurely}
\li{\code{\startverb COMPLETED\stopverb} - Study has concluded}
\li{\code{\startverb WITHDRAWN\stopverb} - Withdrawn prior to enrollment}
}

\p{\strong{Example: Find recently completed trials with results}}

\pre{\startverb
from scripts.query_clinicaltrials import search_studies

results = search_studies(
    condition="alzheimer disease",
    status="COMPLETED",
    sort="LastUpdatePostDate:desc",
    page_size=50
)

# Filter for trials with results
trials_with_results = [
    study for study in results['studies']
    if study.get('hasResults', False)
]

print(f"Found {len(trials_with_results)} completed trials with results")
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{6. Retrieve Detailed Study Information}
\p{Get comprehensive information about specific trials including eligibility criteria, outcomes, contacts, and locations.}

\p{\strong{Example: Extract eligibility criteria}}

\pre{\startverb
from scripts.query_clinicaltrials import get_study_details

study = get_study_details("NCT04852770")
eligibility = study['protocolSection']['eligibilityModule']

print(f"Eligible Ages: {eligibility.get('minimumAge')} - {eligibility.get('maximumAge')}")
print(f"Eligible Sex: {eligibility.get('sex')}")
print(f"\nInclusion Criteria:")
print(eligibility.get('eligibilityCriteria'))
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Example: Extract contact information}}

\pre{\startverb
from scripts.query_clinicaltrials import get_study_details

study = get_study_details("NCT04852770")
contacts_module = study['protocolSection']['contactsLocationsModule']

# Overall contacts
if 'centralContacts' in contacts_module:
    for contact in contacts_module['centralContacts']:
        print(f"Contact: {contact.get('name')}")
        print(f"Phone: {contact.get('phone')}")
        print(f"Email: {contact.get('email')}")

# Study locations
if 'locations' in contacts_module:
    for location in contacts_module['locations']:
        print(f"\nFacility: {location.get('facility')}")
        print(f"City: {location.get('city')}, {location.get('state')}")
        if location.get('status'):
            print(f"Status: {location['status']}")
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{7. Pagination and Bulk Data Retrieval}
\p{Handle large result sets efficiently using pagination.}

\p{\strong{Example: Retrieve all matching trials}}

\pre{\startverb
from scripts.query_clinicaltrials import search_with_all_results

# Get all trials (automatically handles pagination)
all_trials = search_with_all_results(
    condition="rare disease",
    status="RECRUITING"
)

print(f"Retrieved {len(all_trials)} total trials")
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Example: Manual pagination with control}}

\pre{\startverb
from scripts.query_clinicaltrials import search_studies

all_studies = []
page_token = None
max_pages = 10  # Limit to avoid excessive requests

for page in range(max_pages):
    results = search_studies(
        condition="cancer",
        page_size=1000,  # Max page size
        page_token=page_token
    )

    all_studies.extend(results['studies'])

    # Check for next page
    page_token = results.get('pageToken')
    if not page_token:
        break

print(f"Retrieved {len(all_studies)} studies across {page + 1} pages")
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{8. Data Export to CSV}
\p{Export trial data to CSV format for analysis in spreadsheet software or data analysis tools.}

\p{\strong{Example: Export to CSV file}}

\pre{\startverb
from scripts.query_clinicaltrials import search_studies

# Request CSV format
results = search_studies(
    condition="heart disease",
    status="RECRUITING",
    format="csv",
    page_size=1000
)

# Save to file
with open("heart_disease_trials.csv", "w") as f:
    f.write(results)

print("Data exported to heart_disease_trials.csv")
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Note:} CSV format returns a string instead of JSON dictionary.}
}

\subtree{
\title{9. Extract and Summarize Study Information}
\p{Extract key information for quick overview or reporting.}

\p{\strong{Example: Create trial summary}}

\pre{\startverb
from scripts.query_clinicaltrials import get_study_details, extract_study_summary

# Get details and extract summary
study = get_study_details("NCT04852770")
summary = extract_study_summary(study)

print(f"NCT ID: {summary['nct_id']}")
print(f"Title: {summary['title']}")
print(f"Status: {summary['status']}")
print(f"Phase: {', '.join(summary['phase'])}")
print(f"Enrollment: {summary['enrollment']}")
print(f"Last Update: {summary['last_update']}")
print(f"\nBrief Summary:\n{summary['brief_summary']}")
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{10. Combined Query Strategies}
\p{Combine multiple filters for targeted searches.}

\p{\strong{Example: Multi-criteria search}}

\pre{\startverb
from scripts.query_clinicaltrials import search_studies

# Find Phase 2/3 immunotherapy trials for lung cancer in California
results = search_studies(
    condition="lung cancer",
    intervention="immunotherapy",
    location="California",
    status=["RECRUITING", "NOT_YET_RECRUITING"],
    page_size=100
)

# Further filter by phase
phase2_3_trials = [
    study for study in results['studies']
    if any(phase in ['PHASE2', 'PHASE3']
           for phase in study['protocolSection'].get('designModule', {}).get('phases', []))
]

print(f"Found {len(phase2_3_trials)} Phase 2/3 immunotherapy trials")
\stopverb}
}
}

